<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="20" pageNumber="129" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,335,1861,1887]" box="[189,335,1861,1887]" pageId="20" pageNumber="129">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,335,1861,1887]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="20" pageNumber="129" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,335,1861,1887]" pageId="20" pageNumber="129">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,917,1907,1969]" box="[234,377,1907,1934]" pageId="20" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,1908,1934]" pageId="20" pageNumber="129">Male</emphasis>
(n=5)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[189,917,1907,1969]" lastBlockId="22.[188,1400,265,749]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="20" pageNumber="129">
Length: 
<quantity box="[288,388,1942,1969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="20" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
. Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[553,684,1943,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoenix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[553,684,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="129">D. phoenix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[691,782,1943,1969]" pageId="20" pageNumber="129" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
as follows: Frons about 0.28 × head width at level of ocellar triangle; 5–8 well-developed frontal setae reaching level of apex of pedicel; gena and genal groove with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1384,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Dexosarcophaga spp., ♂ and ♀, habitus and terminalia. A. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Mato Grosso, Chapada dos Guimarães, terminalia, lateral view. B–D. Dexosarcophaga sphaera sp. nov., paratypes (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Brasília, Distrito Federal, Fazenda Vargem Bonita. B. ♂, habitus, lateral view. C. ♂, terminalia, lateral view. D. ♀, terminalia, ventral view. E–F. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, paratype (NHRS [lost]), Ecuador, Napo Prov. E. Habitus, lateral view. F. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823748/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
); first flagellomere approximately 4× as long as pedicel; thorax with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity (
<figureCitation box="[198,292,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Dexosarcophaga spp., ♂ and ♀, habitus and terminalia. A. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Mato Grosso, Chapada dos Guimarães, terminalia, lateral view. B–D. Dexosarcophaga sphaera sp. nov., paratypes (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Brasília, Distrito Federal, Fazenda Vargem Bonita. B. ♂, habitus, lateral view. C. ♂, terminalia, lateral view. D. ♀, terminalia, ventral view. E–F. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, paratype (NHRS [lost]), Ecuador, Napo Prov. E. Habitus, lateral view. F. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823748/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
); acrostichals 3 (weakly differentiated) +1; dorsocentrals 3 (anteriormost shorter) + 3 (well differentiated); intra-alars 2 +2; meral setae 5–7; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[845,854,425,439]" fontSize="6" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">1</subScript>
setulose; third costal sector setulose ventrally; abdomen dark brown, with slightly yellowish-silver pollinosity (
<figureCitation box="[941,1063,441,467]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-11@17.[289,1298,265,1783]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. Dexosarcophaga spp., ♂ and ♀, habitus and terminalia. A. Dexosarcophaga petra sp. nov., ♂, paratype (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Mato Grosso, Chapada dos Guimarães, terminalia, lateral view. B–D. Dexosarcophaga sphaera sp. nov., paratypes (MNRJ [lost]), Brazil, Brasília, Distrito Federal, Fazenda Vargem Bonita. B. ♂, habitus, lateral view. C. ♂, terminalia, lateral view. D. ♀, terminalia, ventral view. E–F. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, paratype (NHRS [lost]), Ecuador, Napo Prov. E. Habitus, lateral view. F. Terminalia, lateral view. Scale bars =1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823748" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823748/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 8E–F</figureCitation>
); T4 with 1–2 pairs of lateral marginal setae; row of about 10 marginal setae on T5; short incision along inner margin of ST5 and arms with pad-shaped protrusion (
<figureCitation box="[594,703,511,537]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
); cercal prongs convergent in posterior view and truncated in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[382,526,546,573]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11B–C</figureCitation>
); pregonite as long as postgonite, apical half curved and with spine-like projection (
<figureCitation box="[328,439,582,608]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
); ventral margin of basiphallus with projection (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1145,582,608]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
); vesica stick-like in lateral view and apically enlarged in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[791,933,617,643]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D–E</figureCitation>
); juxta mostly membranous and almost squared (
<figureCitation box="[296,376,652,678]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
D-E); median stylus tube-like with developed projection, shorter than lateral stylus, and with narrow apex (
<figureCitation box="[417,562,687,713]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D–E</figureCitation>
); lateral stylus tube-like, with base twisted towards ventral margin of paraphallus (
<figureCitation box="[340,482,722,749]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
