<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="131" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,304,1001,1027]" box="[189,304,1001,1027]" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,304,1001,1027]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,304,1001,1027]" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1399,1047,1391]" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,464,1047,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,464,1047,1073]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Dexosarcophaga napo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[479,576,1048,1074]" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lopes, 1975" authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1975" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[965,1305,1047,1073]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Dexosarcophaga inaequalis</emphasis>
Lopes, 1975
</taxonomicName>
. Males of both species have a stick-like vesica in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1028,1138,1082,1108]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
; Silva &amp; Mello-Patiu 2010: figs 53–54) and paraphallus with a projected lobe ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1133,1117,1144]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
; Silva &amp; Mello-Patiu 2010: figs 53–54). These two species can be differentiated by the following features: basiphallus with a conspicuous projection at ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[690,798,1188,1214]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
), projected lobe of paraphallus pointing distally in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[341,447,1223,1249]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
), and median stylus with a developed projection (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1155,1223,1249]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[189,232,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[213,1374,297,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-11@21.[200,1387,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 11. Dexosarcophaga napo sp. nov., ♂, holotype (NHRS [lost]). A. Sternite 5, ventral view. B. Syntergosternite 7 +8, epandrium, cercus and surstylus, lateral view. C. Cerci, posterior view. D. Phallus and associated structures, lateral view. E. Distiphallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods. Scale bars =0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6823754" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6823754/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11D–E</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authority="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu, 2022" authorityName="Santos &amp; Pape &amp; Mello-Patiu" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Dexosarcophaga napo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[258,352,1259,1285]" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, versus basiphallus without a conspicuous projection at ventral margin (Silva &amp; MelloPatiu 2010: fig. 53), projected lobe of paraphallus pointing ventrally in lateral view (Silva &amp; MelloPatiu 2010: figs 53–54), and median stylus without a developed projection (Silva &amp; Mello-Patiu 2010: figs 54–55) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lopes" authorityYear="1975" box="[359,692,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Dexosarcophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[359,692,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="131">Dexosarcophaga inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
